      ## Visiting a partner website

      In the trivago iOS app, the final step of the flow is for the user to “clickout”, and visit the partner website to book their  hotel.

      The partner website is presented in a browser within the trivago app. This means that, <em>for the user to navigate back, they simply need to tap the back button</em> in the top left of the screen. But, as it's a browser, there are also browser back/forward buttons displayed on the same screen.

      <em>Having multiple back/forward buttons on the same screen is confusing</em>. So we decided to A/B test presenting the browser view modally, with a close button instead of a back button. But after A/B testing the change, <em>there was a significant drop in users “clicking out” and browsing different hotel prices</em>.

