      ## Conclusion

      Even though I tested multiple variations for “Close”, on the left and right of the screen, the back icon still performed strongest. <em>With 19/40 participants successfully completing the task</em>.

      The <em>back button at the bottom of the screen</em>, as well as the <em>back button displayed on the Hotels.com website</em>, proved to be the main cause of incorrect clicks. And our initial assumption, that “Close” would be clearer, wasn't correct.

